File: The South African flag. Wikimedia Commons JOHANNESBURG - The South African Federation of Trade Unions says ordinary South Africans have nothing to celebrate on Freedom Day.
Saftu says apartheid exposed black people to many injustices such as poor education, cheap labour and unfair discrimination. READ: SA celebrates 27 years of democracy The union says poor people who rely on the government are still subjected to arrests and killings during protests. It has criticised the laying off of over one million people last year. Saftu said the working class must increase its fighting capacity to resist the capitalist's onslaught.